{
  "stem": "9446.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "The Catholic Church in Portland was brainwashing the people who believed that the Jews were murdered by Jesus Christ as many people believe even today, even in the United States.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And that, alone, was the major contributing factor to anti-Semitism in Poland, you know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Most of the Poles are very devout Catholics.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm sorry.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I forgot it-- and how.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I remember I was exposed to classical music so much.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I practically grew up with Caruso and all the greatest singers.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had a lot of records of the greatest symphonies and all that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My father played violin, by the way, as an amateur, and played beautifully.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "One of the-- one of the compositions that is always fresh in my mind, because I love it, number one, and because my father played it is Tchaikovsky's barcarolle called 'Barcarolle Melancolique.' In case you ever have a chance to listen to it, you may find it's a unique experience if you like music.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we Jewish people, most of us, have a special love for music I think-- not necessarily Jewish music.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Music is, in my opinion, very international.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I mean, there are many compositions written by many composers of all nationalities.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that's one thing-- as I was exposed a lot to music-- and languages.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We are kind of born linguists.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I forgot to mention it to you.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Some people have a natural inclination to learn languages.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] Many Jewish people have that ability.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Europe, it is common that a person speaks two or three languages, because of the variety of countries, you know, neighboring here.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[CLEARING THROAT] But in our family it was very typical.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father was a linguist, and he spoke beautiful English, and French, and Russian.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
